      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Do you know I received and returned five saddles, none of which fitted! The last of these to arrive still didn’t fit. The yard owner said “if we use a thick numnah and a prolite wither pad etc etc it should just about fit”. I repeat, this was a brand new made to measure saddle.  At the time I wasn’t in a fit state to make decisions about anything due to my nervous breakdown so I gave up trying and took my horse to France without a saddle.",
